{{Quote|Mandalorian steel is meant for armor, not weapons.|The Armorer|<ref name="Return of the Mandalorian" />}}
'''Beskar''', also known as '''Mandalorian iron''' or '''Mandalorian steel''', was an alloy that was used in [[Mandalorian armor]] and was notable for its high tolerance to extreme forms of damage. In its purest forms, the metal was durable enough to withstand a direct [[blaster]] shot and could repel [[lightsaber]] strikes. A [[superweapon]] created by the [[Mandalorian]] [[Sabine Wren]] and used by the [[Galactic Empire]], called the [[Arc Pulse Generator]], was capable of superheating the metal to the point that it would burn everything it was protecting to a crisp, such as Mandalorian warriors encased within their beskar [[armor]]. However, Wren destroyed her weapon during the [[Mandalorian Civil War (Imperial Era)|Mandalorian Civil War]].

==Description==
Beskar in its pure form<ref name="The Jedi" /> was one of the toughest and most legendary metals in [[the galaxy]].<ref name="Heroes of Mandalore" /> The purest form of beskar<ref name="The Star Wars Book">''[[The Star Wars Book]]''</ref> was capable of repelling the strikes of a [[lightsaber]]<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition" /> for brief amounts of [[time]],<ref name="The Star Wars Book" /> and could withstand direct [[blaster]] fire.<ref name="The Siege of Lothal">{{Rebels|The Siege of Lothal}}</ref><ref name="Gunslinger">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 5: The Gunslinger}}</ref><ref name="Mand9" /><ref name="The Mandalorian Chapter 10">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 10: The Passenger}}</ref> Pure beskar could still be damaged by weapons also made out of beskar; because of this, making weapons out of beskar was considered illegal by the [[Children of the Watch]].<ref name="Return of the Mandalorian" /> The metal could also be reforged to any warrior's liking.<ref name="Heroes of Mandalore" /> Beskar was found only on Mandalorian worlds. In [https://starwars.fandom.com/wiki/Beskar?file=Beskar-TSWB.png ingot] form, beskar was [[Color|silver]] with wavy patterns.<ref name="The Star Wars Book" />

==Usage==
{{Quote|It is amazing how beautiful beskar can be when forged by its ancestral artisans.|"The Client"|<ref name="Chapter 7: The Reckoning">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 7: The Reckoning}}</ref>}}
[[File:Legacy-In-The-Making-LJasonQueen.png|thumb|left|250px|Mandalorian armor across the generations]]
Beskar was a material used by the various groups,<ref name="Mandalore Plot">{{TCW|The Mandalore Plot}}</ref> [[Mandalorian clan|clans]]<ref name="Protector of Concord Dawn">{{Rebels|The Protector of Concord Dawn}}</ref> and [[Mandalorian house|houses]]<ref name="Eminence">{{TCW|Eminence (episode)}}</ref> of [[Mandalore]]'s [[Mandalorian|people]], such as the clans [[Clan Wren|Wren]], [[Clan Vizsla|Vizsla]],<ref name="Heroes of Mandalore" /> [[Clan Saxon|Saxon]],<ref name="Old Friends Not Forgotten">{{TCW|Old Friends Not Forgotten}}</ref> and [[Clan Kryze|Kryze]]; and the [[Nite Owls]],<ref name="Heroes of Mandalore" /> as well as the Children of the Watch. "[[The Armorer]]" used a [[cryo-furnace]], [[magnetic tongs]], and a [[gravity hammer]] in [[Armorer's workshop|her workshop]] to forge armor from beskar.<ref name="The Sin">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 3: The Sin}}</ref> Her tools were made from beskar, and were able to repel strikes from the Darksaber.<ref name="Return of the Mandalorian" /> The Mandalorian method for forging beskar was a closely guarded secret, a skill passed on through generations to keep ancient armor intact and impervious.<ref name="Forge Databank">{{Databank|the-armorer-s-forge|The Armorer's forge}}</ref>

According to Mandalorians, all beskar belonged to them,<ref name="Mand9">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 9: The Marshal}}</ref> but, over the course of history, many other parties claimed it.<ref name="The Sin" /> It was also used for weapons, such as in [[Beskar spear|spears]],<ref name="Return of the Mandalorian" /> [[Cudgel (weapon)|cudgel blades]],<ref name="Script">{{Disney|subdomain=assets.debut|url=documents/Andor%20209%20--%20POST%20FINAL%20--%203.3.24%5B1%5D.pdf|text=Episode #209 "Welcome To The Rebellion" Script|format=PDF}}</ref> traditional ''[[beskad]]'' [[sword]]s, ''[[kal]]'' [[dagger]]s,<ref name="COTR" /> [[Munit'kad halberd|''munit'kad'' halberd]]s,<ref name="Episode IX VD" /> and the hilt of the [[Darksaber]]. Beskar weapons were considered taboo by the Children of the Watch, as they could injure or kill other Mandalorians that had beskar armor.<ref name="Return of the Mandalorian" /> Beskar plates were also used to reinforce strength-enhancing [[glove]]s known as [[crushgaunt]]s that were capable of shattering [[bone]]s as well as turning the blade of a lightsaber.<ref name="COTR" /> On the planet [[Ferrix]], citizens tracked [[time]] by the ringing of a beskar anvil that was ritually struck by the [[Time Grappler]].<ref name="That Would Be Me Audio">{{Andor|That Would Be Me}} {{AD|Disney+}}</ref>

==History==
===Republic Era===
In the [[Standard day|days]] of the [[Galactic Republic|Old Republic]], [[Tarre Vizsla]] created the Darksaber, and its hilt was made from beskar.<ref name="Return of the Mandalorian" /> Due to its unique properties, beskar was used to forge armor capable of repelling Jedi lightsabers during the [[Mandalorian-Jedi War]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition">''[[Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition]]''</ref> Armor forged from beskar was used as early as [[500 BBY]].<ref name="Heroes of Mandalore" /> Before joining the [[Nihil]], the future [[Tempest Runner]] [[Lourna Dee]] took part in bar fights while wearing beskar armor, making her appear Mandalorian whenever her [[lekku]] were not exposed.<ref name="Tempest Runner">''[[The High Republic: Tempest Runner]]''</ref>

[[File:Epguide214.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A [[Unidentified Death Watch assassin|Mandalorian warrior]] of Death Watch]]
During the [[Clone Wars]], [[Death Watch]]<ref name="Mandalore Plot" /> continued to use beskar for their [[Mandalorian armor|armor]].<ref name="The Star Wars Book" /> Members of Death Watch continued using their armor when their faction split in two; one portion of Death Watch became part of [[Maul]]'s [[Shadow Collective]] as the [[Mandalorian super commando]]s, while another banded under [[Lady]] [[Bo-Katan Kryze]] to become the [[Mandalore resistance]].<ref name="Son of Dathomir, Part Three">[[Darth Maul — Son of Dathomir 3|''Darth Maul — Son of Dathomir'' 3]]</ref> During her time with the resistance, former [[Jedi]] [[Padawan]] [[Ahsoka Tano]] was given a Mandalorian-designed combat outfit with beskar plates.<ref name="OFNF EG">{{SW|url=series/clone-wars/old-friends-not-forgotten-episode-guide|text="Old Friends Not Forgotten" Episode Guide &#124; The Clone Wars}}</ref>

At some point in the Clone Wars, the [[assassin]] [[Ochi]] of [[Bestoon]] had a deadblade made of beskar. On Sidious's orders, he attempted to assassinate [[Depa Billaba]] on [[Malathon IX]] but was disarmed of the blade by [[Mace Windu]].

===Imperial Era===
Beskar was among the profitable cargoes recommended to fellow [[smuggler]]s by [[Platt Okeefe]] in the [[pirate]] [[Maz Kanata]]'s ''[[Smuggler's Guide]]'', along with [[corusca gem]]s, [[Quella gem/Canon|quella gems]], and [[prismatic crystal]]s.<ref name="Smuggler's Guide">''[[Star Wars: Smuggler's Guide]]''</ref> An [[Unidentified Arcona bounty hunter|Arcona]] [[bounty hunter]] wore a set of beskar armor.<ref name="Bounty Hunters 6">[[Bounty Hunters 6|''Bounty Hunters'' 6]]</ref> [[Enfys Nest]] had beskar [[Gauntlet shields|gauntlets]].<ref name="Character Encyclopedia">''[[Star Wars: Character Encyclopedia, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref>

[[File:WrenWarrior_TheDuchess_Beskar_HeroesOfMandalorePart2.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The Arc Pulse Generator targets a Clan Wren warrior's beskar armor]]
While a [[cadet]] at the [[Imperial Academy of Mandalore]], [[Sabine Wren]] constructed the [[Arc Pulse Generator]]. Invented as a challenge, the "[[Duchess]]" was designed to target the beskar in Mandalorian armor and heat it up to the point where it got so hot that it vaporized the wearer. Upon realizing that the [[Galactic Empire]] had tested the weapon on her own people and intended to keep using it, Wren sabotaged the weapon, destroyed the plans, and fled, eventually joining up with the [[Spectres]], a band of rebels who later became part of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. Although Wren believed she had destroyed her weapon, the Empire salvaged and rebuilt it, although they were unable to restore it to its full power. Rumors spread that the Empire had tested such a weapon, but there was never confirmation among other Mandalorian clans that the Duchess was real.<ref name="Heroes of Mandalore" />

Eventually, a [[Mandalorian Civil War (Imperial Era)|civil war]] broke out after Clan Wren rebelled against Clan Saxon, which had been placed in power by [[Darth Sidious|the Emperor]], and [[Governor]] [[Tiber Saxon]] attempted to use the Arc Pulse Generator, fitting it onto the [[AT-DP Arc Cannon Prototype]]. After [[Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo|Thrawn]] suggested that Saxon capture Wren to restore the weapon to its full capacity, Saxon [[Mission to Mandalore|laid a trap]] for Wren and the [[Mandalorian resistance]] aboard [[Tiber Saxon's Star Destroyer|his]] [[Star Destroyer]]. However, Wren and Bo-Katan Kryze destroyed the weapon for good after Wren reprogrammed it to target the [[plastoid]] in [[stormtrooper armor]], and the weapon's detonation also killed Saxon.<ref name="Heroes of Mandalore" />

===Post-Great Purge===
{{Quote|The Beskar belongs back into the hands of a Mandalorian.|"The Client"|<ref name="Mando1" />}}
[[File:BeskarSpear-SWL98_Ryan_Valle.png|thumb|right|300px|Din Djarin defeated Moff Gideon in personal combat wielding a beskar spear.]]
During the [[Great Purge of Mandalore]], the Empire took beskar<ref name="Mando1" /> as spoils<ref name="The Sin" /> after killing the majority of the Mandalorians.<ref name="Mando6">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 6: The Prisoner}}</ref> After the fall of the Empire, beskar was harder to come by.<ref name="Databank">{{Databank|beskar|beskar}}</ref> In [[9 ABY]], an Imperial known as "[[the Client]]" gave bounty hunter [[Din Djarin]] a piece of the beskar imprinted with the [[Imperial crest]] taken from the Mandalorians during the purge, which he then used to forge a new shoulder plate for himself and gave the excess to the Armorer for future [[foundling]]s.<ref name="Mando1" /> Later, after capturing a [[Din Grogu|child]] of the [[Yoda's species|same species]] as Jedi [[Grand Master]] [[Yoda]], the Client gave a [[camtono]] of beskar to Djarin in payment. He then used the Beskar to forge a new set of armor for himself and once again gave the excess to [[The Tribe]]'s foundlings.<ref name="The Sin" /> [[Morgan Elsbeth]] had in her possession a [[beskar spear]] which she used in combat against [[Ahsoka Tano]]. The [[spear]] was then gifted to Din Djarin after the [[Liberation of Calodan|liberation]] of [[Calodan]].<ref name="The Jedi">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 13: The Jedi}}</ref> The spear was later reforged into [[Grogu's chainmail shirt|armor]] for Grogu, as the armorer considered it dangerous to Mandalorians.<ref name="Return of the Mandalorian" />

[[Gideon]] later created the [[Dark Trooper phase 4|next-generation armor for the Dark Trooper]] from beskar alloy.<ref name="Chapter 23" /> The former Imperial [[Sentinel]], who played the part of a loyal stormtrooper in the [[Hunters of the Outer Rim]] competition,<ref name="BftA">''[[Hunters: Battle for the Arena]]''</ref> owned a suit of beskar [[snowtrooper armor]] identified as the "Beskar Buckethead" suit. Sentinel claimed to deserve the armor and remarked that it felt very good.<ref name="SWHunters">''[[Star Wars: Hunters]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The name "beskar" originated in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] article ''[[The Mandalorians: People and Culture]]'', published in ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' in [[2006]] and written by [[Karen Traviss]].<ref name="PAC">{{InsiderCite|86|The Mandalorians: People and Culture}}</ref> Before that, it was known as Mandalorian iron. It was first introduced unnamed, in the form of [[Mandalorian manacles]], in the Legends comic [[Tales of the Jedi 5|''Tales of the Jedi'' 5]],<ref name="T5">[[Tales of the Jedi 5|''Tales of the Jedi'' 5]]</ref> and was later named Mandalorian iron in the comic [[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 2|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 2]].<ref name="DL">[[Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith 2|''Tales of the Jedi – Dark Lords of the Sith'' 2]]</ref>

[[Boba Fett's armor]] was previously stated to be made of [[durasteel]].<ref name="VisNewEdition">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary, New Edition]]''</ref> However, "[[Chapter 14: The Tragedy]]" of ''The Mandalorian'' [[Retroactive continuity|retconned]] the Fett armor into being made of beskar.<ref name="Chapter14">{{TheMandalorian|Chapter 14: The Tragedy}}</ref>

